### Dev Race Control — synthetic timing & race lifecycle
### Requires VS Code REST Client extension (humao.rest-client)
###
### Seed credentials (all passwords: Racer1Pass!)
###   director@example.com  — RACE_DIRECTOR + REFEREE
###   admin@example.com     — ADMIN
###
### Seed transponder numbers: 101–106 (racer1–racer6)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api/v1

# ── 1. Login — run this first, token is captured automatically ───────────────

# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "director@example.com",
  "password": "Racer1Pass!"
}

###

@token = {{login.response.parsedBody.accessToken}}

# ── 2. Fire a synthetic lap passing (random entry in the race) ───────────────
# Replace 5 with the actual race ID shown in the run order sidebar.
# Call repeatedly to simulate multiple drivers completing laps.

POST {{baseUrl}}/dev/race/5/synthetic-passing
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ── 3. Race lifecycle commands ───────────────────────────────────────────────

# Call Grid (PENDING → GRID)
POST {{baseUrl}}/race-control/race/5/call-grid
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# Start Race (GRID → RUNNING)
POST {{baseUrl}}/race-control/race/5/start
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# Stop Race (RUNNING → STOPPED)
POST {{baseUrl}}/race-control/race/5/stop
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# Resume Race (STOPPED → RUNNING)
POST {{baseUrl}}/race-control/race/5/resume
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# Finish / Abandon Race (RUNNING or STOPPED → FINISHED)
POST {{baseUrl}}/race-control/race/5/finish
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

# ── 4. Run order (GET — no auth required) ───────────────────────────────────

GET {{baseUrl}}/event/1/run-order
